    <section class="epic-destinations">
        <h2>Check out these epic destinations!</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Torna Fort</h3>
                    <img src="torna.jpg" alt="Torna Fort" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">
                    <p>Torna Fort, also known as Prachandagad, is a historic hill fort in Maharashtra, famous for being the first fort captured by Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj in 1643.
                         Situated at an elevation of 1,403 meters, 
                         it offers stunning views of the Sahyadri range and is a popular destination for trekkers and history enthusiasts.</p>

                         <a href="/treking" class="btn">Trekking</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Kalsubai</h3>
                    <img src="kalsubai.webp" alt="Torna Fort" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">
                    <p>Kalsubai is the highest peak in Maharashtra, standing at 1,646 meters (5,400 feet) in the Sahyadri range. Known as the "Everest of Maharashtra," it is a popular trekking destination, offering panoramic views of the surrounding valleys and forts. 
                        The summit also features a small temple dedicated to the local deity Kalsubai.</p>
                        <a href="/hiking" class="btn">Hiking</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-content">
                    <h3>Pawna Lake</h3>
                    <img src="pawna.jpg" alt="Torna Fort" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">
                    <p>pawna Lake, located near Lonavala in Maharashtra, is a popular destination for camping enthusiasts. Surrounded by lush hills and historic forts, the lake offers a serene and picturesque setting for camping, with activities like bonfires, stargazing, and boating.
                         It's a perfect getaway for nature lovers and those seeking a peaceful retreat.</p>
                         <a href="/camping" class="btn">Camping</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

